caption.p: Overview of cells found in a bronchoalveolar lavage sample from two healthy cynomolgus macaques. (A) macaque #1, (B) macaque #2. Alveolar macrophages (MÏ†) predominate, followed by lymphocytes (L). Neutrophil (N) and occasional ciliated columnar epithelial cells (E) are also present. Modified Giemsa. X50 objective. Oil immersion.
